{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.11",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 11 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:1",
      "text": "A false balance is an abomination to the Lord, but a just weight is his delight.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:2",
      "text": "When pride comes, then comes disgrace; but with the humble is wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:3",
      "text": "The integrity of the upright guides them, but the crookedness of the treacherous destroys them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:4",
      "text": "Riches do not profit in the day of wrath, but righteousness delivers from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:5",
      "text": "The righteousness of the blameless keeps his way straight, but the wicked falls by his own wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:6",
      "text": "The righteousness of the upright delivers them, but the treacherous are taken captive by their lust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:7",
      "text": "When the wicked dies, his hope perishes, and the expectation of the godless comes to naught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:8",
      "text": "The righteous is delivered from trouble, and the wicked gets into it instead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:9",
      "text": "With his mouth the godless man would destroy his neighbor, but by knowledge the righteous are delivered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:10",
      "text": "When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices; and when the wicked perish there are shouts of gladness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:11",
      "text": "By the blessing of the upright a city is exalted, but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:12",
      "text": "He who belittles his neighbor lacks sense, but a man of understanding remains silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:13",
      "text": "He who goes about as a talebearer reveals secrets, but he who is trustworthy in spirit keeps a thing hidden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:14",
      "text": "Where there is no guidance, a people falls; but in an abundance of counselors there is safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:15",
      "text": "He who gives surety for a stranger will smart for it, but he who hates suretyship is secure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:16",
      "text": "A gracious woman gets honor, and violent men get riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:17",
      "text": "A man who is kind benefits himself, but a cruel man hurts himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:18",
      "text": "A wicked man earns deceptive wages, but one who sows righteousness gets a sure reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:19",
      "text": "He who is steadfast in righteousness will live, but he who pursues evil will die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:20",
      "text": "Men of perverse mind are an abomination to the Lord, but those of blameless ways are his delight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:21",
      "text": "Be assured, an evil man will not go unpunished, but those who are righteous will be delivered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:22",
      "text": "Like a gold ring in a swine's snout is a beautiful woman without discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:23",
      "text": "The desire of the righteous ends only in good; the expectation of the wicked in wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:24",
      "text": "One man gives freely, yet grows all the richer; another withholds what he should give, and only suffers want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:25",
      "text": "A liberal man will be enriched, and one who waters will himself be watered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:26",
      "text": "The people curse him who holds back grain, but a blessing is on the head of him who sells it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:27",
      "text": "He who diligently seeks good seeks favor, but evil comes to him who searches for it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:28",
      "text": "He who trusts in his riches will wither, but the righteous will flourish like a green leaf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:29",
      "text": "He who troubles his household will inherit wind, and the fool will be servant to the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:30",
      "text": "The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life, but lawlessness takes away lives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.11.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:31",
      "text": "If the righteous is requited on earth, how much more the wicked and the sinner!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
